years refer to West Germany only. Inflation: annual percentage growth in
consumer prices. Interest rates: nominal long-term government bond
yields. Unemployment rate: percentage of the civilian labour force.
Government balance: the net lending (+) or net borrowing (-) of general
government as a percentage of GDP. Debt: the gross debt of general
government as a percentage of GDP. 1992 Figures for inflation, bond
yields and unemployment are averages over year to date. (Generally
Jan-Oct). Figures for the Government balance and Debt are European
Commission forecasts. Source: European Commission.
