<TEXT>
Gun battles raged in suburbs of the Tajik capital yesterday with Islamic
guerrillas stepping up hit-and-run attacks two days after the arrival of a
new government in Dushanbe, Reuter reports from Dushanbe.
The guerrillas set ablaze fuel storage tanks and fought with ex-communist
gunmen in the city's southern Islamic stronghold of Avul where a senior
Russian army officer said six people were killed in clashes which knocked
out a thermal station providing much of the heating of the city.
