<HEADLINE>
FT  12 DEC 92 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Severance payment
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I recently accepted early severance from my employer. The financial package
was a lump sum amounting to Pounds 60,000. There were no other compensatory
payments. On the lump sum, I was taxed approximately Pounds 21,500, as a
considerable amount was at 40 per cent. Come April, I will be able to
calculate the tax due for 1992/3 based on total earnings. I am writing about
'top slicing.' I have never understood the implications. Can I take
advantage of it?
Unfortunately, top-slicing relief does not apply to severance payments like
yours.
